      <div rendition="class:83225 maturity:83211" type="edition" xml:lang="san-Latn">
        <!-- 
Comments below by Csaba Kiss and Dániel Balogh (BD) are offered "as is" and do not represent a thoroughly researched or considered opinion. 
-->
        <!-- 
SEAL has only image of dog? 
-->
        <p><!-- 
I treat the daṇḍas in brackets in the edition as supplied. 
--><pb n="1v"/><lb n="1"/>jayati bhagavāñ jinendro guṇa-rundraḫ prathita-parama-kāru<!-- 
L1. FN:"The word 'svasti' seems to have been engraved before 'jayati,' but to have been cut off in shaping the plate; so that only part of the second syllable can be seen in the margin." 
--><lb break="no" n="2"/>ṇikaḥ trailokyāśvāsa-karī dayā-patākocchritā yasya||
<lb n="3"/>śrī-viṣṇuvarmma-prabhr̥tīn narendrāN nihatya jitvā pr̥thivīṁ sama<unclear>stāṁ</unclear>
<lb n="4"/>Utsādya kāñcīśvara-caṇḍadaṇḍaM palāśikāyāṁ samavasthitas saḥ<supplied reason="subaudible">.</supplied>
					<pb n="2r"/><lb n="5"/>raviẖ kadamboru-kulāmbarasya guṇāṁśubhir vyāpya jagat sama<unclear>staṁ</unclear>
<lb n="6"/>mānena catvāri nivarttanāni dadau jinendrāya mahī<supplied reason="omitted">M</supplied> mahendraḥ<supplied reason="subaudible">.</supplied>
<lb n="7"/>saṁprāpya mātuś caraṇa-prasādaṁ dharmmaika-mūrtter api dāmakīrtteḥ
<lb n="8"/>tat-puṇya-vr̥ddhy-arttham abhūn nimittaM śrī-kīrtti-nāmā tu ca tat-kaniṣṭhaḥ||
					<pb n="2v"/><lb n="9"/>rāgāt pramādād athavāpi lobhāT yas tāni hiṁsyād iha bhūmi-
<lb n="10"/>pāla Ā-saptamaṁ tasya kulaṁ kadāciT nāpaiti kr̥tsnān nirayān nimagnaM<supplied reason="subaudible">.</supplied><!-- 
L10. Is there a visara after pāla? 
--><lb n="11"/>tāny eva yo rakṣati puṇya-kā<surplus>ṁ</surplus>ṅkṣaḥ sva-vaṁśa-jo vā para-vaṁśa-jo vā
<lb n="12"/>sa modamānas sura-sundarībhiḥ ciraṁ sadā krīḍati nāka-pr̥ṣṭhe||
					<pb n="3r"/><lb n="13"/>Api coktaṁ manunā</p>
        <lg met="anuṣṭubh" n="1">
          <!-- 
v1. See this verse (with slight variation) in the MBh, supplementary passages to Asvamedhikaparvan: 14.004.1125. 
-->
          <l n="a">bahubhir vvasudhā dattā</l>
          <l n="b">rājabhis sagarādibhiḥ</l>
          <l n="c"><lb n="14"/>yasya yasya yadā bhūmiḥ</l>
          <l n="d">tasya tasya tadā phalaM||</l>
        </lg>
        <lg met="anuṣṭubh" n="2">
          <!-- 
v2. See this verse (with slight variation) in the MBh, supplementary passages to Asvamedhikaparvan: 14_004_1109 
-->
          <l n="a"><lb n="15"/>sva-dattāṁ para-dattāṁ vā</l>
          <l n="b">yo hareta vasundharāM</l>
          <l n="c"><lb n="16"/>ṣaṣṭiṁ varṣa-sahasrāṇi</l>
          <l n="d">niraye sa vipacyate||</l>
        </lg>
